reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Spotless Shine, Miele Approved: Finish All in 1 Gelpacs Nail It!
reviews.reviewText: Finish All in 1 Gelpacs Orange Dishwasher Detergent Tablets are a game-changer for my Miele machine! These little powerhouses have impressed me with their exceptional cleaning performance and efficiency.Using them in my Miele dishwasher has been a revelation. These Gelpacs dissolve quickly and completely, leaving no residue behind. Even with hard water, these tablets ensure sparkling clean dishes without any water spots or streaks.What I appreciate most is their effectiveness on tough stains and dried-on food. They effortlessly tackle grease and grime, leaving dishes, glasses, and utensils spotless. Plus, the orange scent they release during the wash cycle leaves a subtle, refreshing aroma without being overpowering.The convenience of the pre-measured Gelpacs is a bonus, ensuring the right amount of detergent every time. With 84 tablets in a pack, it's a cost-effective option that lasts for several cycles, offering great value for money.Moreover, I've noticed that these tablets are gentle on my machine's components. They don't leave any residue or buildup, ensuring the longevity of my Miele dishwasher.Overall, Finish All in 1 Gelpacs Orange Dishwasher Detergent Tablets have earned their spot as my go-to detergent for a pristine clean in my Miele dishwasher. If you're seeking a reliable and efficient solution for your dishes, these tablets are an absolute win. Highly recommended for their cleaning prowess and Miele compatibility!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works great, doesn’t leave any white residue, which is why I purchased it. I have tried finish, and cascade 3 in 1 and both have left white residue on my dishes, I used hard water booster, and the jet dry (or equivalent) and still had it. I use the big bottles of gel stuff, but tired of messy caps, and heavy bottles. Or not being able to find them, or get a good deal without buying in bulk or at sams club or BJ’s.. I also hate wasting so much of it in the bottom of the bottle because I have no patience to wait for it to make it out of a huge bottle… or shake the heck out of it… so these were a perfect option!!!!They do everything that the liquid gel bottles do without the waste, I can find them on sale, and they are much cleaner and easier to use. And when my osteoarthritis or my psoriatic arthritis kicks in it’s nice not to have to try to lift and squeeze that big gel bottle that’s 1/2 full or 1/4 full to get it out..

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars stick on this one now
reviews.reviewText: I have tried many similar product and some of them have very fancy designs and claim how good they work. Honestly I couldn't see too much difference on the outcome in terms of cleanliness among all products I have used, maybe because my dished are not way too greasy or creamy or dirty in some other way. I like this one more not only because it's affordable. I usually let my dishes dry by itself after wash, and some other brands will have some strange scents when I open the dishwasher right after wash but before drying, this one has no strange scent after wash. However, this product is easy to glue to each other if they get damp. And now I keep them in dry place and always pick the tablet with dry hands, and never has this issue again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Have used for a year...
reviews.reviewText: I have used these dishwashing pods for a year now and I am pretty happy with them. It doesn't leave film on dishes except if the dishes are oriented in an odd way. if any water is unable to drain the residue and film are obvious. Not sure why colors or smells needed to added since it does not impact the finished wash in any way that I can tell. I took a star off for that because I don't like additives I don't need.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not as chemically of a smell which is why I buy these orange ones
reviews.reviewText: The lemon ones are good too. Other kinds, I can't abide the chemical smell in using them or coming out of the dishwasher. I'm hypersensitive (fibromyalgia.) They do a great job and of not getting water spots too. These are my go-to pods as a dishwasher soap solution. Oh, btw, the reason TV commercials keep telling us to rinse the dishes every day in the dishwasher is because new dishwashers seem to be more energy efficient which is code for not doing the job for which they are intended. Sure enough, my water bill went up, not down. I might start using these more often to make up for the dishwasher not doing its job. Maybe that will help. These do a great job from all I've tried, so I'm sticking with them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This was delivered quickly and is just as pictured. Good value for the money. Powder detergents leave a residue on my glasswear, but this product does not. Will definitely buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cleaning, no film/residue
reviews.reviewText: These are so good. I had to quickly get some more pods as I was running out and my usual subscribe and save wouldn’t get to me fast enough. I grabbed these since they’d arrive overnight. I’m really pleasantly surprised and switched my subscription. I’ve had an issue with a soapy residue / film left on the dishes and I thought it was the dishwasher. It’s a bit older and I thought maybe it just doesn’t rinse thoroughly anymore. But I haven’t noticed that issue the last week or so using these cute little squishies.Not really a noticeable scent for me though it says orange. I think it’s just really light and fresh so if you’re sensitive to scented things these would probably be a good choice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: As your typical millennial, I use Kirkland brand because my dad picks it up for me when he goes to Costco.(Yes, I do pay for it) I purchases this because my parents were out of town when I realized I needed more. Fearing the outdoor world, this was what I went with. Did not get dishes clean all the time. Definitely does not stand up to Kirkland, but you still don’t have to wash dishes by hand. So, 3 stars.

I absolutely love these dishwasher pods. They clean my dishes perfectly. I don’t like tablets with powder so I have been using these since the day I got my dishwasher. Someone complained that they don’t clean well, I think that’s more so of a dishwasher problem and not these tablets also, you can not take them out of the box with wet hands as that makes the casing dissolve and they stick together. So I always dry my hands first. Seems like a little common sense. Highly recommend!
This dishwasher soap works amazing and smells awesome. No harsh chemicals/bleach so never fades any patterns on dishes.
Works Good especially for the price compared to the high end Pods.
